description:
When Dutch hikers Kris Kremers and Lisanne Froon vanished in Panama, search teams discovered a camera with over 130 photos. The first 50 were normal  smiling faces, trail markers, scenic vistas. But after April 8th, everything changed. Between 1:00 and 4:00 AM, more than 90 photos were taken in darkness. Some show rocks, branches, and what looks like blood on a leaf. One image appears to show Kriss head, partially lit. Another  the most haunting  seems to depict a body posed under foliage, partially buried. These photographs remain some of the most disturbing clues in true crime history.
